news.title: Kalpataru Projects International net profit down 3% to Rs 139.59 cr
news.para: The company had a consolidated net profit of Rs 144.07 crore in the quarter ended December 31, 2023, the company said in a regulatory filing. The total income of the company rose to Rs 5,742.76 crore in the quarter under review, from Rs 4,909.95 crore in the same period a year ago.

news.title: Bihar government to launch new portal for construction workers
news.para: Labour resources minister Santosh Kumar Singh announced the initiative on Thursday, highlighting the transparency and convenience it will bring.

news.title: Government eyes UDCPR extension for Pune metropolitan region
news.para: The proposal received initial approval from chief minister Devendra Fadnavis during Wednesday's development authority's first meeting for PMRDA in Mumbai and an official notification regarding this is expected to follow soon.

news.title: Punjab government to create economically weaker sections housing over 1,500 acres
news.para: Under the scheme, scattered land pockets located in different housing colonies will be sold off and the money raised would be utilised to acquire 1,500-acre land in different cities of the state.

news.title: Mormugao PDA told to check permissions of Bhutani project in Sancoale
news.para: The MPDA has been given 15 days to look into the concerns raised by GBA. MPDA will have to look for evidence of non-compliance, missing or misrepresented information.

news.title: Only 22% work done in housing project for urban poor in Vadodara
news.para: The housing scheme on the Harni-Warasiya Ring Road was planned as a public-private partnership (PPP) project.

news.title: MHADA to develop online system for lease deed, conveyance in Mumbai
news.para: This is being undertaken as part of the Maharashtra government's 100-day action plan, under which Chief Minister Devendra Fadnavis and Deputy Chief Minister & Housing Minister Eknath Shinde have directed administrative reforms to enhance citizen services.

news.title: MHADA to conduct structural audit of 1,000 cessed buildings in Mumbai by March-end
news.para: MHADA Vice President and CEO, Sanjeev Jaiswal has instructed the officials to accelerate the process to ensure the timely completion of this structural audit.

news.title: Over 4,500 houses in DLF 1-5 to face action for illegal construction in Gurugram
news.para: The bench, comprising Justices Sureshwar Thakur and Vikas Suri, issued a verdict, directing the district administration and DTCP to implement measures within two months and submit an action-taken report by April 19, 2025.

news.title: Lucknow development body reopens e-auction portal to sell 300 plots
news.para: Online registrations will be allowed till March 10 and the e-auction will be conducted on March 17.

news.title: Rajasthan RERA revises fees for projects in Jaipur
news.para: According to the revised structure, registration fee remains unchanged at Rs 5 per square metre for residential, institutional, industrial, and farmhouse categories.

news.title: Consumer court in Coimbatore asks builder to return Rs 7 lakh to customer
news.para: According to an official source, M S Soundararajan, of Edayarpalayam, approached a construction firm at Vilankurichi to build an office on the first floor of his house.

news.title: Divisional commissioner orders for FIR against builders in Lucknow
news.para: A total of 30 complaints related to several issues concerning property, encroachment and other matters were received during the hearing, of which 8 were resolved on the spot.

news.title: HCC posts consolidated loss of Rs 38.92 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: Hindustan Construction Company's total income in the third quarter of the ongoing fiscal declined to Rs 1,066.16 crore, as against Rs 1,512.37 crore in the corresponding period of the last fiscal.

news.title: Hong Kong's government plans to crack down on inadequate housing
news.para: Hong Kong's government is planning to crack down on what it calls inadequate housing in subdivided apartments, mandating a minimum size and other baseline standards for homes like Au's.

news.title: Greater Mohali development body committed gross violations: NGT
news.para: The NGT was hearing a matter regarding the authority allegedly committing violations of the environmental clearance (EC) conditions in its housing project, Purab Premium Apartments in Mohali.

news.title: Allahabad HC gives relief to owners of 81 apartments facing demolition in Lucknow
news.para: On the suggestion of the Lucknow Development Authority (LDA), the bench permitted the owners to apply to the authority for compounding their flats by depositing the requisite penalty, according to the court order.

news.title: UltraTech Cement commissions 0.6 MTPA cement capacity in Tamil Nadu
news.para: This expansion will help the company’s ability to meet the growing demand for composite cement in the Southern region enhancing its blended cement ratio.

news.title: Kamdhenu Ventures net profit drops 51.35% in Q3 FY25
news.para: The company's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 74.19 crore in Q3 FY25, a dip of 6.28 per cent from Rs 79.16 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.
